defaultGreen Community Champions (GCC)
default             
defaultT
defaulthe Council made an open call to citizens to ask them if they would like to be green community champions and asked them to define what they wanted to do, supported by a single officer. There are now 500 champions working with over 60 groups and 5,000 residents on local environmental issues – from food growing to community energy projects. It has led to more innovation and community ownership than if the 
defaultc
defaultouncil had 
defaultdefined the network 
defaultat the outset. 
