defaultMade in Lambeth
defaultM
defaultade 
defaulti
defaultn 
defaultL
defaultambeth
default is a council facilitated hack-day type event 
defaultwhere
default volunteers work together over single weekends to address particular challenges within the borough.  Volunteers come from a range of backgrounds including graphic designers, artists, project managers and community organisers.  Projects they have worked on include designing a brand new website and branding for the Young Lambeth Coop, accelerating the approach to digital inclusion across the borough, re-launching Vauxhall City Farm and marketing affordable pay-day loan products from the London Mutual Credit Union.  The council facilitates these events through coordinating project briefs and providing a location and 
defaultwifi
default.  However, the output is very much down to those who take part in the weekends.  This approach has enabled the council to harness the creativity of communities and helped create a more permissive council culture where creative changes 
defaultdesigned by the community are put into practice.
defaultCommunity 
defaultFreshview
defaultCommunity 
defaultFreshview
default is a community-led opportunity for residents to make a difference to their local area whether through brightening up a green space, giving a disused space a facelift or any other activity that improves the local environment.  The council provides nominal support such as plants and paint, expertise where needed
default,
default and support in accessing additional volunteers.  In addition to sprucing up an area Community 
defaultFreshview
default has the benefit of bringing neighbours together and has been undertaken by more than 20 separate groups already.  This example has emphasised the value 
defaultof 
defaultproviding a clear and simple 
defaultoffer
default of council support for resident-led activity and highlighted how barriers to participati
defaulton can be overcome through well 
defaultpublicised council support.
defaultEvidencing what worksdefault and learning from early projects. defaultBrixton Energy
defaultBrixton Energy is a not-for-profit co-operative based in Lambeth creating cooperatively owned renewable energy projects whose financial revenues stay within the local community. It is the first social-housing based renewable energy company in the country with a vision to create a greener future for Brixton.  In doing so it is generating energy, increasing Brixton’s energy 
defaultresilience and security, raising awareness about energy efficiency
default,
default tackling fuel poverty
default,
default and providing training and employment for local people.  It was established in cooperation with the council.  Since then five further roofs on the estate have been fitted with panels.
defaultConclusion defaultThese are challenging times; 
defaultthere is less funding and an increased d
defaultemand for some public services.
default 
defaultT
defaulthere are risks but there are opp
defaultortunities too. The Lambeth approach is transformational bu
defaultt we have achieved this through
default a solid evidence base of support (through our Cooperative Council Commission)
default; 
default citizen engagement
default;
default and early prototyping to develop our thinking and draw learning around issues of risk, organisational structure, accountability, behaviour change and capacity building. We have found that in order for the approach to work, the council must help mitigate risk
default,
default but more importantly by building new relationships and putting the citizen in control we are saving money. Ultimately 
defaultwe believe that we will 
defaultsee a collaborative community
default in Lambeth
default where the council acts as a platform for
default that
default collaboration, providing the right spaces and infrastructure to make 
defaultit
default happen. By empowering local people in this way we can give them back the power to change their lives and help those around them, fostering stronger more resilient communities. 
